15/12/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- During a visit to Skopje on Tuesday (14 December), NATO Director for the Balkans Robert Serry expressed support for government efforts to handle the issue of armed militants in the village of Kondovo. 
Following closed-door talks with Prime Minister-designate Vlado Buckovski, Serry said he doubted the issue would lead to destabilisation.
In other news, EU security chief Javier Solana announced on Tuesday that the Union has decided to extend its police mission in Macedonia by one year. 
The force trains local police to combat organised crime and enforce law and order along Macedonia's borders. 
(Vest, Dnevnik - 15/12/04; Macedonian government Web site, A1 TV, Makfax, AFP, Reuters - 14/12/04)
